_:Nc7b622beca69412e916775a9af6d06aa <http://schema.org/description> "The Northern Lighthouse Board is the General Lighthouse Authority for Scotland and the Isle of Man. It provides marine navigation aids to assist the safe passage of mariners through waters in these areas. It is also responsible for marking and dispersing wrecks which are a danger to navigation. NLB is an executive non-departmental public body, sponsored by the Department for Transport ." .
